            <title>[LUCENE-589] Demo HTML parser doesn&apos;t work for international documents</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-589</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;Javacc assumes ASCII so it won&apos;t work with, say, japanese documents. Ideally it would read the charset from the HTML markup, but that can by tricky. For now assuming unicode would do the trick:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add the following line marked with a + to HTMLParser.jj:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;options {&lt;br/&gt;
  STATIC = false;&lt;br/&gt;
  OPTIMIZE_TOKEN_MANAGER = true;&lt;br/&gt;
  //DEBUG_LOOKAHEAD = true;&lt;br/&gt;
  //DEBUG_TOKEN_MANAGER = true;&lt;br/&gt;
+  UNICODE_INPUT = true;&lt;br/&gt;
}&lt;/p&gt;</description>
